      <link>http://feeds.conversationsnetwork.org/~r/channel/itc/~3/oYGR4MypeYU/detail5141.html</link>
      <description>An &amp;#039;app-in-store&amp;#039; model is a dramatic shift from the bulky but comfortable advantages of a big corporate website, where large, constant refreshing or redeployment of the site&amp;#039;s entire content happens up to 30 times everyday. Dion Almaer, Ben Galbraith expound on how Android technology is influencing big retail, including Wal-mart.&lt;div class="feedflare"&gt;
